     <h2 class="text-center pc mb-4 font-weight-bold">Types of Cancer We Treat</h2>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div class="container">
  <div class="item-box text-center">
   <div class="department">
    <div class="row">
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 first bg-blue">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="61" height="75" src="images/icons/breast-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Breast Cancer" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Breast Cancer</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Breast cancer is the leading cancer in women worldwide and can affect men, although it's rare.</p>
         <p>> Symptoms often involve the presence of lumps, alterations in breast size or shape, and nipple discharge.</p>
		 <p>> Early detection through regular mammograms and self-exams is important.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 ">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="74" height="68" src="images/icons/ovarian-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Ovarian Cancer" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Ovarian Cancer</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Ovarian cancer, though relatively rare, is a serious condition affecting the ovaries.</p>
         <p>> Symptoms may include abdominal discomfort, bloating, changes in bathroom habits, fatigue, and unexplained weight loss.</p>
		 <p>> Discussions with a healthcare provider about appropriate screening methods is necessary.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 bg-blue">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="68" height="63" src="images/icons/kidney-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Kidney Cancer" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Kidney Cancer</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Kidney cancer, or renal cancer, originates in the kidneys and can progress quickly if not caught early.</p>
         <p>> Symptoms may include blood in the urine, persistent lower back pain, and unexplained weight loss.</p>
		 <p>> It's essential to schedule regular check-ups, especially if you have risk factors.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 last">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="74" height="68" src="images/icons/bladder-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Bladder Cancer" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Bladder Cancer</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Bladder cancer begins in the lining of the bladder and requires vigilant monitoring.</p>
         <p>> Symptoms may include blood in the urine, frequent urination, and pain or discomfort during urination.</p>
		 <p>> Recognizing these symptoms and promptly seeking medical evaluation are crucial for early detection and treatment.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 first">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="74" height="68" src="images/icons/head-neck-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Head-Neck Cancers" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Head-Neck Cancers</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Head and neck cancer includes cancers affecting the head and throat region, often linked to risk factors like tobacco and alcohol use.</p>
         <p>> Persistent symptoms may include neck swelling, sore throat, mouth ulcers, lumps in the neck, jaw or mouth, and hoarseness.</p>
		 <p>> Immediate medical attention is necessary if the symptoms last more than two weeks.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 bg-blue">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="74" height="68" src="images/icons/lung-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Lung Cancer" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Lung Cancer</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Lung cancer originates in the lungs and can affect both smokers and non-smokers.</p>
         <p>> Symptoms may include a persistent cough, chest pain, shortness of breath, and unexplained weight loss.</p>
		 <p>> Quit smoking and seek medical evaluation for concerning symptoms.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="74" height="68" src="images/icons/prostate-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Prostate Cancer" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Prostate Cancer</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> A type of cancer that develops in the prostate gland, which is a part of the male reproductive system.</p>
		 <p>> Common symptoms may include frequent urination , difficulty urinating, pain or discomfort in the pelvic area.</p>
		 <p>> Early detection through regular screenings, like the PSA test, is crucial.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 last bg-blue">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="74" height="68" src="images/icons/Gi-cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="GI Cancers" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">GI Cancers</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Gastrointestinal (GI) cancer encompasses a range of cancers affecting the digestive system.</p>
		 <p>> Symptoms often include abdominal pain, alterations in bowel habits, blood in stool, unexplained weight loss, loss of appetite, difficulty swallowing, and nausea/vomiting.</p>
		 <p>> Regular screenings are key to early detection and treatment.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="col-md-3 m-0 px-0">
      <div class="dt-sc-icon-box type6 first bg-blue">
       <div class="icon-wrapper"><img width="74" height="68" src="images/icons/blood cancer.webp" class="attachment-full" alt="Blood Cancers" decoding="async" loading="lazy"></div>
       <div class="icon-content">
        <h4 class="title font-weight-bold">Blood Cancers</h4>
        <div class="tret-cntnt">
         <p>> Blood cancer, including leukemia, lymphoma, and myeloma, affects blood and bone marrow cells.</p>
		 <p>> Symptoms vary depending on the specific type but can include fever, fatigue, weakness, bone and joint pain, swollen lymph nodes, and anemia.</p>
		 <p>> Early diagnosis and appropriate treatment strategies are essential.</p>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
