    <div class="wow fadeInUp">
     <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">What are the common types of cancer treated in oncology?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">Oncology includes the treatment of different types of cancers, such as breast cancer, colorectal, prostate, ovarian, lung cancer, solid tumors, and hematologic malignancies (blood cancers).</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">What is the role of a multidisciplinary team in oncology?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-3">A multidisciplinary team of healthcare providers plays an important role in oncology. The team usually includes oncologists, surgeons, radiologists, pathologists, nurses, and other specialists in supportive care. Nurses and other specialists in supportive care are also included. They work together to provide holistic care for the patients by creating comprehensive treatment plans.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">How can I reduce the risk of cancer?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">Lifestyle changes can reduce the risk of cancer. It is important to maintain a healthy body weight, consume a diet high in fruits and veggies, engage in regular physical exercise, avoid excessive alcohol and tobacco consumption, prevent infections (such as human papillomavirus or hepatitis), as well as stay up-to-date with cancer screenings and vaccines. Also, consult healthcare professionals to get personalized advice on cancer prevention.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">How does the Oncology Department personalize treatment plans for patients?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">The Oncology Department at Star Hospitals takes into account each patient’s unique circumstances, including their medical history, current symptoms, and lifestyle, to personalize their treatment plan. Advanced molecular and genomic tests like Next generation Sequencing(NGS) are run on individual biopsy samples and specific treatment is formulated to each patient. Our team of expert oncologists strives to involve patients in every step, ensuring that they understand their medical condition and treatment options.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">How does the Oncology Department provide support for patients and their families?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">The Oncology Department at Star Hospitals provides comprehensive support for patients and their families, including emotional and psychological support, nutritional counseling, and pain management. We also have a dedicated team of social workers who help our patients to access resources and support services in the community.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">How does the Oncology Department collaborate with other specialists to provide care?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">The Oncology Department at Star Hospitals collaborates with other specialists, including surgeons, radiation oncologists, and pathologists, to provide comprehensive care for our patients. We work together to create a personalized treatment plan that addresses each patient’s unique needs. For example, there is a weekly “Multidisciplinary Tumor Board(MDT)” where individual cases are discussed and a comprehensive treatment plan is formulated.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">What is the approach of the Oncology Department to end-of-life care?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">The Oncology Department at Star Hospitals provides compassionate end-of-life care by providing advanced pain and palliative care facilities. We work closely with our patients to understand their goals and wishes and also offer comprehensive symptom management and emotional support to them and their families.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6">
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">What are the treatment options available in oncology?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">Treatment options in oncology depend on the type and stages of cancer. These include Surgery, radiotherapy, chemotherapy, targeted therapies, immunotherapy, and hormone therapy. Treatment is tailored according to the patient's needs.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">What are the risk factors for developing cancer?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">Several factors can increase the risk of cancer, including age and family history. Other factors include tobacco, alcohol consumption, poor lifestyle choices, and certain infections. Knowing and addressing these factors is crucial to reduce the risk of cancer.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">What types of cancer does the Oncology Department at Star Hospitals treat?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">The Oncology Department at Star Hospitals in Hyderabad treats all types of cancer, including Breast Cancer, Lung Cancer, Prostate Cancer, Brain Cancer, Bone Cancer, Colon Cancer, Sarcomas, Melanoma, Head and Neck Cancer, and Blood Cancers like leukemia, lymphoma, Multiple Myeloma.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">What types of diagnostic tools and technology does the Oncology Department use?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">The Oncology Department at Star Hospitals invests in the latest diagnostic tools and technology, including imaging studies like CT scans, MRI, PET scans, and blood tests to help diagnose and monitor cancer progression. We provide molecular testing and advanced pathology testing in the form of Immunohistochemistry(IHC). The latest treatment options such as chemotherapy, radiation therapy, and immunotherapy are also available.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">Can the Oncology Department help patients in managing the side effects of cancer treatment?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">Yes, the Oncology Department at Star Hospitals is expertise in managing the side effects of cancer treatment. We provide personalized care plans that address each patient’s side effects and offer comprehensive symptom management support. Round the clock support system is provided to the patients for managing the side effects, if any.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">Is the Oncology Department at Star Hospitals involved in the research and clinical trials?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">Yes, the Oncology Department at Star Hospitals is involved in research and clinical trials to advance the field of cancer treatment. Our team of expert oncologists is committed to staying at the forefront of cancer treatment by offering our patients access to the latest clinical trials and research studies.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="shadow faqheader mb-4 bg-white round-20px wow slideInUp">
        <div class="question tc">Does Oncology Department at Star Hospitals has a Genetic clinic?</div>
        <div class="answercont">
         <div class="answer">
          <p class="mb-0">The Oncology Department at Star Hospitals has a dedicated genetic clinic that offers genetic counseling and advanced genomic testing. If any genetic mutation is detected, cascade testing of the family members is done after which reconstruction surgeries and risk-reducing surgeries in the form of bilateral mastectomies are offered.</p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
